    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 10. Statistischer UIP-Test: Regression\n",
    "\n",
    "Der klassische empirische Test der UIP nutzt folgende Regression:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\underbrace{\\Delta s_{t+1}}_{\\text{tats. Kursänderung}} = \\alpha + \\beta \\cdot \\underbrace{(i_{US,t} - i_{EU,t})}_{\\text{Zinsdifferenzial}} + \\varepsilon_{t+1}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Was erwartet die UIP?**\n",
    "- $\\alpha = 0$ (kein systematischer Trend)\n",
    "- $\\beta = 0.25$ (quartalsmäßig: 1/4 des Jahreszinsdifferenzials)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Das „Forward Premium Puzzle":** Empirisch findet man oft $\\hat{\\beta} < 0$ – also das Gegenteil der UIP-Prognose. Hochzinswährungen werten *auf* statt ab."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Regression schätzen\n",
    "reg <- lm(delta_s_actual ~ zins_diff, data = df)\n",
    "summary(reg)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualisierung der Regression\n",
    "beta_hat <- coef(reg)[2]\n",
    "alpha_hat <- coef(reg)[1]\n",
    "\n",
    "ggplot(df, aes(x = zins_diff, y = delta_s_actual)) +\n",
    "  geom_point(size = 3.5, color = \"#1f77b4\", alpha = 0.8) +\n",
    "  geom_text(aes(label = format(qstart, \"%Y Q%q\")),\n",
    "            vjust = -0.8, size = 3, color = \"#333333\") +\n",
    "  geom_smooth(method = \"lm\", se = TRUE,\n",
    "              color = \"#d62728\", fill = \"#f7b6b6\", linewidth = 1.2) +\n",
    "  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 0.25,\n",
    "              linetype = \"dashed\", color = \"#2ca02c\", linewidth = 1.2) +\n",
    "  annotate(\"text\", x = Inf, y = Inf,\n",
    "           label = paste0(\"OLS: beta = \", round(beta_hat, 3)),\n",
    "           hjust = 1.1, vjust = 1.5, size = 4.5, color = \"#d62728\") +\n",
    "  annotate(\"text\", x = Inf, y = -Inf,\n",
    "           label = \"UIP: beta = 0.25\",\n",
    "           hjust = 1.1, vjust = -0.5, size = 4.5, color = \"#2ca02c\") +\n",
    "  labs(\n",
